pageContext.claim: “You ever noticed with Biden, he’s always calling the wrong state? ‘And in your great state of Iowa, Iowa. It’s Iowa, right?’ ‘No, it’s Wisconsin.’ ‘Oh, I meant Wisconsin. Oh, I didn't know I was in Wisconsin.’ … You know the sad part about that? When you do that, you can't really recover.”
pageContext.analysis: The New York Times noted: "In reality, Mr. Trump has also suffered his share of confusion about his speaking locations or where tragedies have occurred under his watch. In a somber, televised speech in August after two mass shootings, for instance, Mr. Trump blessed 'the memory of those who perished in Toledo,' referring to a city more than 100 miles away from Dayton, the scene of an Ohio massacre."
